The government on Monday started cultivating 2,000 acres in Kilifi county to cushion the elderly from the effects of drought.Kilifi is one of the counties that was worst-hit.The 2,000 elderly people will each have one acre cultivated by the government free of charge.Agriculture PS Richard Lesiyampe said they have identified the beneficiaries. &ldquo;We have subcontracted our Agricultural Mechanical Services to take charge of screening for all the marginalised families and small-scale elderly farmers,&rdquo; he said. Lesiyampe spoke on Saturday in Mwanjama after he and Mining CS Dan Kazungu distributed 20,000 tonnes of maize seeds and 2,000 bags of fertiliser.